subject: Notifications support and sample listeners
commitMessage:
Notifications support and sample listeners

- Enable support for notifications for mount/umount events
- Notifications can be enabled/disabled at build time (default is disabled)
- Sample notifications' listener is added as well
- Notifications may be extended (if possible) in future to enable/disable automounting based on user preference
- Added sample mount listener

Change-Id: Ieeaf2da37d05e84461cfffc601a38ad38e9f288f
Signed-off-by: Imran Zaman <imran.zaman@intel.com>

User=app is added because multiple instances of udisks-automount-agent keeps running even if the user is logged out. For example, initially when the image boots up, there is one instance of agent with user 'app' started. When ssh is made using 'tizen' user, another instance of agent starts up. Even ssh for 'tizen' user is closed, still 2 agents keep running.. 

There is no core-efl.target exists for IVI.

I can revert the changes so that agent is added to the user session with new target of 'core-efl.target' in IVI. Is it possible to know that how can it be then added to IVI specific target e.g weston so that it gets kicked in automatically..
